{"name":"Yvonne - The Spirit Who Longs for Revenge","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-embers-orange.webp","system":{"npcType":"dark_presence","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Yvonne was a ragged little orphan who survived on the streets of Paris by selling candles. Scorned by all, even by the poor who saw her only as a burden, she found compassion in only one person: Father Adrien, a young priest who offered her work, shelter, and kindness. One evening, Yvonne discovered Adrien's secret laboratory where he distilled absinthe for illegal sale. Fearing his sin would be exposed, Adrien strangled the girl into unconsciousness, set her on fire to hide his crime, and threw her charred remains into the catacombs. What was found the next day was a small, burned body with only one part intact: her teeth, shining white and locked in a deathly grin. Many poor people who depended on Adrien witnessed the murder but kept silent to preserve his favor and the small wages he paid them. Thrown into a mass grave without ceremony, Yvonne was reborn that night as a vengeful spirit. She now wanders the Catacombs of Paris, tormenting those who were silent at her murder with maddening laughter and vicious whispers. When her victims light a flame to see who hides in the darkness, Yvonne feeds the fire and sets them ablaze, burning them alive just as she was burned. She is methodically killing everyone who knew her murderer but said nothing, saving Father Adrien for her grand finale. With the passage of the comet Morituris on December 31st, Yvonne plans to channel the mystical energy into the Cemetery of the Innocents' mass graves, creating an inferno that will burn all of Paris—a city that allowed her to die alone and forgotten.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":3,"max":3},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire","I am a child who was betrayed by everyone I trusted","My laughter echoes through the darkness before I strike","My teeth shine white in a permanent deathly grin"],"gifts":[{"name":"Spirit","description":"Yvonne exists in spirit form and is extremely difficult to permanently harm. **Immunity to Physical Damage:** Yvonne can only truly be damaged by magic, blessed weapons, or supernatural attacks. Normal physical weapons pass through her. **Life Drain Touch:** The touch of Yvonne's spirit form absorbs life energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers cannot defend against this Gift—armor, shields, and walls are useless. **Regeneration:** If Yvonne is harmed by non-magical means, she still suffers Wounds temporarily. However, when reduced to 0 Wounds by non-magical attacks, she disappears and rematerializes immediately with all Wounds healed (except those inflicted by magical means, which persist). **Summon Spirits:** Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits to her aid who will obey her will for the duration of the Scene."},{"name":"Soul of Fire","description":"Yvonne can manipulate fire at will, a dark reflection of how she died. This Gift only affects flames that are already lit—she cannot create fire from nothing, but she can feed and control existing flames with terrifying power. **Fire Manipulation:** Controlling fire is considered an additional action for Yvonne, allowing her to attack and manipulate flames in the same turn. **Fire Attack:** Yvonne-controlled fire inflicts 1 Wound on hit. If the Defense Check is an Outcome with a Cost, the target continues to burn. **Continued Burning:** During the following Exchange, if not extinguished, the fire inflicts 1 additional Wound automatically. This continues each Exchange until put out. **Amplification:** Yvonne can multiply the width and size of any flame by up to ten times, turning a candle into a bonfire or a torch into a inferno. **Tactical Use:** Yvonne's strategy is to make victims light torches or candles to see in the dark catacombs, then feed those flames to immolate them alive."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Get revenge on Father Adrien and all those who ignored my death and kept silent","Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead using the comet Morituris' power","Make them all feel the flames that consumed me"],"notes":"Yvonne is a tragic villain—an innocent child murdered and abandoned, transformed into an instrument of vengeance. Voice: Childish laughter that becomes increasingly manic and bitter, whispers in the darkness. Appearance: Small child-sized spirit, charred and burned, with only her teeth gleaming white in a permanent grin. Strategy: Stalks victims in dark catacombs, laughs and whispers to frighten them into lighting flames, then feeds those flames to burn them alive. Hit List: Killing methodically—one person per night who witnessed her murder. Olivier is her final victim before Adrien. Schedule: December 31st is crucial—comet Morituris passes, giving spirits mystical energy. Plans to use Mass of Restless Spirits in Cemetery of Innocents to explode and burn Paris. Can be redeemed: If Hunters allow her revenge on Adrien (who deserves it—he murdered a child), Yvonne will help prevent the cemetery explosion. Won't forgive Adrien but might spare Paris if justice is served. Mechanically: Requires magic to truly harm. Fire manipulation makes her deadly but predictable—extinguish flames to weaken her. Can summon 3-9 Restless Spirits depending on scene. Mass of Restless Spirits mechanic: Grudge Tokens accumulate (start at 2, comet adds 1 at midnight). If 3+ tokens when comet passes, explosion wipes out half of Paris. Spiritualist Alizée or magic-users can remove tokens. Complex morality: Victim seeking justice vs. spirit planning mass murder. Hunters must judge both her and Adrien."},"flags":{"darkPresence":true,"presenceType":"antagonist-redeemable","inspiration":"The Little Match Girl by Hans Christian Andersen + vengeful spirit","role":"Child spirit seeking revenge through fire for her murder and abandonment","historicalNote":"Catacombs of Paris and Cemetery of the Innocents"},"_id":"fe9a82971a5b6c43"}